  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study in humans with stable coronary artery disease (CAD) treatable by
      percutaneous intervention (PCI) is to evaluate the efficacy of Enhanced External
      Counterpulsation (EECP) with regard to coronary collateral growth.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
